      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., normalised RMS error) applied to hemolysis index predictions vs. experimental measurements across all 5 operating points; metric must demonstrate adequate agreement at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Output comparison was performed using a visual overlay of CFD predictions against experimental data points on a hemolysis index vs. flow-rate plot. The assessment team noted good qualitative agreement and reported mean absolute error of 8.3%. However, no formal quantitative comparison metric (normalised RMS, U95 uncertainty bands, or equivalent) was computed and documented in the credibility evidence package. The comparison relies on graphical inspection rather than a defensible numerical agreement criterion, which is insufficient to satisfy Gradation 2 for Output comparison under ASME V&V 40. This factor therefore achieves only Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2."
    },
