      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index) directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion and is computed from CFD shear stress history using a validated power-law damage accumulation model.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index is the direct regulatory acceptance metric (RH < 1 vs. predicate). It is computed via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model applied to Lagrangian particle shear stress histories extracted from the CFD solution. Direct correspondence between computational QoI and clinical decision criterion established. Exceeds MRL 2 requirement."
    },
